---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Mission | MindMotion"
  description="Make robots safe to deploy around people. MindMotion builds runtime safety software for AI-driven robots."
>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main">
    <Section id="mission" heading="Mission" headingLevel={1}>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg md:text-xl text-accent-2 leading-snug">
        Make robots safe to deploy around people
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="approach"
      heading="Approach"
      variant="tinted"
    >
      <p>
        Capability and trust are different problems. The brain of a robot
        becomes more capable through better data and more training. Trust
        does not come from the same place. Trust comes from outside the
        brain: a layer between the brain and the body, that keeps the body
        under control, independent of what the brain decides.
      </p>
      <p>
        The brain is free to imagine and evolve, but the layer between the
        brain and the body holds. We build that layer.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section id="founder" heading="Founder">
      <p>
        MindMotion, Inc. is led by David Braun. He has spent more than
        fifteen years working on robot control, the field that makes robot
        motion predictable and reliable. His research has produced methods
        for controlling complex robots in the real world, including humanoid
        systems he built and tested.
      </p>
      <p>
        He holds a Ph.D. in mechanical engineering. His work has been
        recognized with the NSF CAREER Award.
      </p>
    </Section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
